{
  "stem": "26465.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I was looking around, and all of a sudden, it dawned upon me that people were doing it all-- all over.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the stench was horrible-- even though it was rain-- the rain dispersed a little bit of it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But when we came into that room, the wet undergarments stank terribly.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And you-- you could just choke.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "People were just gasping for breath-- couldn't manage.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And some people were fainting, and in that fainting pose, they simply fell asleep, finally.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because they were too tired-- and so did I, and so did my friend, Helen.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were there about three days.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because, what did I do after I woke up?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I decided that I can't take it anymore.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I forgot that, OK, we were separated before getting into that room-- so I was separated by-- with my friend Helen was taken to the other side, because we were trying to help this older lady who was fainting.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the kapo grabbed my friend Helen by the collar and took her to the other side of the triangle-- triangle-- the quadrangle.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was left alone.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So when I was left alone-- alone, I was so traumatized, I decided-- if I could just-- when I looked at this-- the third floor, the ramp, I said, I am going to jump, and finish with it.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "When we were taken back into the courtyard in the morning, I tried this.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And some older man grabbed me by the-- from the back, and took me-- tried to take me away from-- from the side of the ramp.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the gestapo noticed that, and he came and grabbed me.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
